      "Phase 3 is about what comes next. And what comes next is the most important part, because this is where the Donroe Doctrine stops being a military campaign and becomes a permanent structure. A shield. An alliance. A hemisphere that belongs to the people who live in it... not to Beijing, not to Moscow, not to the cartels, and not to the bureaucrats in Brussels or the United Nations who think they get a vote. They don’t. This is our neighborhood. And we just took it back.",
      "The Shield of the Americas",
      "Yesterday... literally yesterday, as I’m writing this... President Trump stood at his golf club in Doral, Florida, surrounded by the presidents of twelve Western Hemisphere nations, and signed a proclamation committing every one of them to a joint military campaign against the cartels and narco-terrorist organizations that have been ripping this hemisphere apart for decades. Twelve countries. Think of that. Argentina, Bolivia, Chile, Costa Rica, the Dominican Republic, Ecuador, El Salvador, Guyana, Honduras, Panama, Paraguay, and Trinidad and Tobago. Twelve presidents standing with Donald Trump. The Shield of the Americas.",
      "And he told them exactly what the deal was. No ambiguity. No diplomatic hedging. No carefully worded communiqué drafted by a committee of State Department lawyers who’ve never been south of Bethesda. He said the only way to defeat the cartels is by unleashing the power of our militaries. That’s a quote. Unleashing the power of our militaries. When was the last time you heard a sitting American President say that to a room full of Latin American leaders? When was the last time twelve of them nodded?",
      "Now. People will say... the critics, the usual crowd... they’ll say Brazil wasn’t there. Mexico wasn’t there. Colombia wasn’t there. And that’s true. They weren’t. And you know why? Because Brazil is playing footsie with Beijing... Lula went to a summit in China in May where Xi pledged a nine-billion-dollar credit line to Latin American nations, trying to fill the void. Because Mexico is the epicenter of cartel violence... the President said it himself, and he’s right... and Claudia Sheinbaum won’t do what needs to be done. Because Gustavo Petro in Colombia has been called an illegal drug leader by the President of the United States, and whether you think that’s fair or not, Petro wasn’t getting an invitation to Doral.",
      "But here is what the critics miss. The critics always miss the same thing. They count the people who aren’t in the room and ignore the people who are. Twelve nations representing over three hundred million people just signed on to a joint military coalition against narco-terrorism under American leadership. That hasn’t happened since the Cold War. Since the Rio Treaty. Since the days when the Western Hemisphere was understood to be an American sphere of influence and everybody accepted it because the alternative was the Soviet Union.",
      "The alternative now is China and Russia. And these twelve countries just chose America. That is the story. That is the headline. And nobody in the media will write it that way, because the media is incapable of seeing good news when Donald Trump is the one delivering it.",
      "Ecuador: The Proof of Concept",
      "Four days before the summit, on March 3rd, something happened in Ecuador that will be studied in military academies for decades. Ecuadorian and American forces launched joint operations against Designated Terrorist Organizations in the Ecuadorian Amazon. General Francis Donovan... the Commander of U.S. Southern Command, a Marine, a serious person... called it a powerful example of the commitment of partners in Latin America and the Caribbean to combat the scourge of narco-terrorism.",
      "By Friday, Ecuadorian and American security forces had attacked a refuge belonging to the Colombian illegal armed group Comandos de la Frontera in the Amazon. A training camp. A rest area for their leader, a man they call Mono Tole. And President Noboa... Daniel Noboa, a young guy, very impressive, very tough... he said this joint fight is only the beginning. Only the beginning. Think about what that means.",
      "That means a sitting Latin American president, operating with full domestic political support, invited the United States military into his country to conduct combat operations against foreign terrorist organizations, and then stood in front of cameras and said he wants more. That is a tectonic shift. That is the opposite of everything that has happened in this hemisphere for the last forty years, where the standard posture of every Latin American government was to tell Washington to stay out, mind your own business, we’ll handle it ourselves. They didn’t handle it. The cartels metastasized. Ecuador went from one of the safest countries in South America to a warzone in less than five years. Noboa looked at what happened, looked at what Trump was offering, and made the smart call.",
