      "China tried to block the deal. Beijing demanded that COSCO, its state-owned shipping company, get a stake. They told state firms to halt new projects in Panama. They threatened to reroute cargo. They called it kowtowing to American pressure. And what did Mulino do? He said Panama is a rule-of-law country, he firmly rejects Beijing’s statement, and the Supreme Court’s decision is final. Think about that. The President of Panama told the People’s Republic of China to take a walk. When has that ever happened in Latin America? When has a small country with four million people stared down Beijing and said no? It happened because the United States was standing behind him. That’s what American power does when it’s actually applied. Not power on paper. Not power in a speech at the UN. Real power, with real consequences, backing a real ally who made the right decision.",
