      "Russia knew the operation was coming. The Wall Street Journal reported that Moscow was aware of an impending military operation against Venezuela but declined to notify China. Didn’t even tell their supposed ally. Chinese diplomats met with Maduro in Caracas less than twenty-four hours before Delta Force stormed his compound, and Beijing had no idea. So much for the infinite friendship.",
      "And when the S-300s failed to fire... when every piece of Russian military hardware in Venezuela folded in hours against two hundred American special operators... Russian military bloggers were writing about it with something between humiliation and grudging respect. Because they watched what Trump did in Caracas and they compared it to what Putin tried to do in Kyiv in February 2022... the botched airborne assault on Hostomel Airport, the forty-mile convoy that got stuck in the mud, the three-day war that became a three-year meat grinder. The contrast was devastating for Russian credibility.",
      "Syria fell in December 2024. Assad gone. Russian naval base at Tartus... threatened. Iran got hit on February 28th. The regime that was supplying Russia with Shahed drones for the Ukraine war... headless. And Venezuela... Russia’s last significant foothold in the Western Hemisphere... captured in a single night. Three of Putin’s key allies neutralized within fourteen months. And Russia couldn’t save any of them. Not one. Because Russia is bleeding out in Ukraine and everybody knows it. The Primakov Doctrine is dead. Russia cannot project power into the Western Hemisphere. They cannot deter American military action. They cannot protect their allies. They cannot deliver oil to Cuba. They cannot maintain weapons systems in Venezuela. They cannot do anything except issue condemnations from Moscow and go back to the war they’re losing in Eastern Europe.",
